Enter Input : another province, where he had gone upon some small piece of business in
Enter Input : company with a Jew. Though Fyodor Pavlovitch was a drunkard and a vicious
Enter Input : debauchee he never neglected investing his capital, and managed his
Enter Input : business affairs very successfully, though, no doubt, not
Enter Input : over-scrupulously. Sofya Ivanovna was the daughter of an obscure deacon,
Enter Input : and was left from childhood an orphan without relations. She grew up in
Enter Input : the house of a general’s widow, a wealthy old lady of good position, who
Enter Input : was at once her benefactress and tormentor. I do not know the details, but
Enter Input : I have only heard that the orphan girl, a meek and gentle creature, was
Enter Input : once cut down from a halter in which she was hanging from a nail in the
Enter Input : loft, so terrible were her sufferings from the caprice and everlasting
